  </figure>

  <h2>Wireframing</h2>
  <p>
    I built rough Sketch wireframes to organize the layout and user flows for
    what was becoming a very complex application — ingestion status, quality
    reports, issue investigation, and state-by-state comparison all needed to
    coexist without overwhelming users.
  </p>

  <figure>
    <img src="/images/nuna/wire1.png" alt="Wireframes — dashboard" />
  </figure>
  <figure>
    <img src="/images/nuna/wire2.png" alt="Wireframes — file detail" />
  </figure>
  <figure>
    <img src="/images/nuna/wire3.png" alt="Wireframes — quality reports" />
  </figure>

  <h2>Refinement</h2>
  <p>
    The final design uses a scalable, multi-level navigation that leaves room
    for future feature expansion. Operators can drill from a fleet-wide view
    of all 57 jurisdictions down into a single file's quality report in a
    handful of clicks.
  </p>

  <figure>
    <img src="/images/nuna/master.png" alt="Master controller" />
  </figure>

  <h2>Outcome</h2>
  <p>
    I presented an Axure prototype at CMS headquarters in Baltimore. The
    reception was exceptional — enough to make it into production planning
    almost immediately. Today, 42 states use the Operations Dashboard in
    full production.
  </p>

  <figure>
    <img src="/images/nuna/final.gif" alt="Nuna Operations Dashboard in use" />
  </figure>
</CaseStudyLayout>
